# TCM-FM2L Manual

1. Download and install Ubuntu 18.04 desktop version.

2. For the example, the ID is &#39;tfarm&#39; and Password is &#39;12345&#39;.

3. Select this option to install automatically.

4. After executing &#39;sudo nano /etc/sudoers&#39;, add the following comment: &#39;tfarm ALL=NOPASSWD: ALL&#39; in &#39;suders&#39; file.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

5.If you can&#39;t log in automatically, do the following.

 (1) After pressing &#39;WINDOW KEY&#39;, input &#39;SETTINGS&#39; on &#39;SEARCH&#39; bar. Click &#39;SETTINGS&#39; application icon.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 (2) After clicking DETAILS menu, click &quot;Users&#39; and then click the &#39;USERS UNLOCK&#39; menu on the upper right corner.

 (3) set up &#39;ON&#39; of &#39;Automatic Login&#39;

6. Unzip the provided minor program..

 (1) unzip dckec.zip

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

(2) You can mine Smart Cash, Max Coin and Creative Coin in the &#39;1dckecsmc&#39; directory.

(3) You can mine Zen Protocol in the &#39;2dckeczp&#39; directory

7. How to check if the server is normally connected with the boards

 (1)   cd 1dckecsmc/ccminer

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

 (2)  Execute this command: &#39;lspci | grep -i xilinx&#39;

     For example, slot 2 and slot 4 are connected.

8. Edit device.txt in order to set up &#39;ccminer program&#39; to recognize the FPGA boards

(1) nano devices.txt

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

(2) setting example for slot 2 and slot 4

/sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:02:00.0/resource0

             /sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:04:00.0/resource0

9. How to execute &#39;Smart Cash&#39; program

(1) Set up and verify Wallet

-- Wallet address can be created in &#39;smartcash.cc&#39;

After running &#39;nano smartcash.sh&#39;, edit like the below example for being enable of &#39;pcidevice&#39;. Next, set the wallet address (see: orange color) and the worker name (for example: &#39;tfm2ml&#39;). And then save and exit.

If the slot 2 and slot 4 are connected, the below two comment lines must be included:

/sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:02:00.0/enable

/sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:04:00.0/enable

However, the below comment line is not matter if they are in &#39;smartcash.sh&#39;.

/sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:01:00.0/enable /sys/bus/pci/devices/0000:06:00.0/enable

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

1. (2)Run Smart Cash shell

sudo ./smartcash.sh

1. (3)After confirming the running, it is possible to check the 2.5gh in the pool after 30 minutes. You can search for &#39;workers stats&#39; on the left of Smart Cash URL: https://us-mine.smartcash.cc/

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

For example, you can access you wallet URL of Smart Cash like [https://us-mine.smartcash.cc/workers/SUpxxxxxxx](https://us-mine.smartcash.cc/workers/SUpxxxxxxx). &#39;SUpxxxxxxx&#39; means your wallet address.

10. How to make it run automatically when you start your computer

(1) Create &#39;start.sh&#39; shell file in any directory and make it run automatically when the computer restarts.

(2) Example of creating start.sh under &#39;/home/tfarm&#39;

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

Run &#39;nano start.sh&#39; and insert the following executable script.

cd /home/tfarm/1dckecsmc/ccminer

sudo ./smartcash.sh

(3) Register &#39;start.sh&#39; above to be executed automatically when login to account.

After pushing button &#39;window key&#39; and finding &#39;startup application&#39; of Search bar,

click &#39;add&#39; button and run &#39;Startup Application Preference&#39;. Next,  type &#39;gnome-terminal - /home/tfarm/start.sh&#39; in &#39;command&#39; of &#39;Startup Application Preference&#39; window and then restart after saving.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

11. Run Vivado\_lab

(1) After running &#39;Vivado\_lab&#39;, click &#39;Open Hardware Manager&#39; and the following screen will be displayed. At this time, click &#39;Auto Connect&#39; icon for connecting a Board.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

(2) When the FPGA board is properly connected, the following screen appears.

If not, the platform driver is not recognized by Ubuntu.

 ![](data:image/*;base64,)

(3) If the FPGA board is not properly connected, reinstall the platform cable driver in Ubuntu.

&#39;cd /tool/Xilinx/Vivado\_lab/2018.3/data/xicom/cable\_drivers/lin64/install\_script/install\_drivers/&#39;

&#39;sudo ./install\_drivers&#39;

The driver will be installed as shown below.
